-- Taiwan Equity Movers: Far Eastern, Pegatron Corp., Tatung Co.
-- B y   G a n   Y e n   K u a n
-- 2012-03-22T05:59:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-22/taiwan-stocks-far-eastern-formosa-international-xxentria.html
Shares of the following companies
had  unusual  moves in  Taiwan trading . Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close in Taipei.  The benchmark Taiex Index rose 1 percent to 8,059.94, its
steepest increase since March 14.  Far Eastern New Century Corp. (1402)  (1402 TT) climbed 0.9 percent
to NT$34.15, its biggest gain since March 13. The textile
company proposed a cash dividend of NT$1.70 per share and a
stock dividend for 2011 earnings, it said in a statement.  Pegatron Corp. (4938)  (4938 TT), a maker of Apple Inc.’s iPhones,
surged 7 percent to NT$45.40, a record close. The company
reported fourth-quarter net income of NT$1 billion ($34
million), beating analysts’ estimates of NT$771 million.  Tatung Co. (2371)  (2371 TT), a maker of electrical and computer
products, gained 1.8 percent to NT$9.64, the most since Feb. 23.
The company may attract investments from Chinese developers for
vast land it owns after Taiwan eases curbs on Chinese
investments, the Liberty Times reported. Tatung declined to
comment, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
